projects.title: Fixed Income Team: Asymmetric Credit Hedge
projects.description: This pitch outlines a complex three-leg derivative structure designed to play into policy uncertainty and economic stress. Rather than a simple directional bet, my team and I built a relative value strategy that balances interest rate volatility, corporate credit risk, and duration hedging.

projects.title: Equity Team: Salesforce (CRM)
projects.description: This equities pitch presents a bullish outlook on Salesforce (CRM), arguing that the market is undervaluing its long-term cash flow profile and its pivot into autonomous AI. The thesis focuses on the companys transition from a standard CRM provider to a core enterprise automation platform with massive scalability.

projects.title: Futures Team: U.S. Softwood Lumber Futures
projects.description: This bullish pitch on Lumber futures targets a recovery in the U.S. housing market driven by an anticipated pivot in Federal Reserve interest rate policy. My team and I analyzed how lower mortgage rates and a chronic domestic housing shortage act as catalysts for demand, while incorporating a technical framework of Moving Averages and RSI to time the entry against supply-side constraints.

projects.title: Fixed Income Team: 10-Year Treasury Note Futures
projects.description: This pitch presents a bullish outlook on 10-year Treasury Note futures (TYH6), anticipating a significant decline in long-term yields as the U.S. labor market cools. The strategy centers on the Federal Reserves transition to a rate-cutting cycle in response to rising unemployment (4.3% as of August 2025) and moderating wage growth, which are effectively easing long-term inflation pressures.

projects.title: Futures Team: Short Palladium Futures
projects.description: This commodity pitch presents a bullish outlook on Palladium futures, focusing on structural supply deficits and geopolitical risks within the PGM (Platinum Group Metals) market. My team and I analyzed the impact of mining disruptions in South Africa and Russia alongside a recovery in automotive demand to project a price rebound, using Relative Strength Index (RSI) and Volume Profile to identify key accumulation zones.

projects.title: Futures Team: Chinese Stainless Steel
projects.description: In this pitch, our team proposes a bullish long on Chinese stainless-steel futures (ZST10), driven by a $169.81 billion stimulus package and a 19.8% year-over-year surge in export volume. I used Bollinger Bands and Weighted Moving Averages for technical timing while hedging our currency risk with a USD/YUAN forward contract.

projects.title: Futures Team: Long JPY/USD Futures Strategy
projects.description: This bullish pitch on Japanese Yen futures (JY3) capitalizes on a fundamental shift in policy divergence between the Federal Reserve's rate cuts and the Bank of Japan's exit from negative rates. My team and I modeled the unwinding of the $350 billion yen carry trade using interest rate parity and Fibonacci retracements to target a recovery driven by cooling U.S. macro indicators

projects.title: Finance Internship 2025 - Barbell + Hedge
projects.description: During my internship at Richwood Bank, I developed a strategic proposal to optimize a $14.92 million fixed income portfolio. After analyzing macroeconomic drivers like Core PCE and unemployment trends, I identified a window to pivot holdings ahead of anticipated Fed rate cuts. I proposed a Barbell + Hedge Approach: liquidating Municipal and Mortgage-Backed Securities to reallocate 57% into short-term, high-quality anchors for liquidity and 30.16% into long-duration 10-year tranches to capture upside from falling rates. To amplify the position, I integrated a Treasury Future Hedge using 15 contracts of 10-year notes.

projects.title: Cluster Project (School) - Buddy Builder Candy
projects.description: The Cluster project at Ohio University is an intensive, integrated business curriculum where student teams collaborate on a massive, semester-long project to develop a comprehensive business concept from scratch. For my project, my team and I created Buddy Builder Candy Lab, a DIY candy-making kit designed to provide families with a screen-free, interactive experience that blends creativity with STEM learning. As the financial lead, I performed deep-dive analysis into our five-year projections, calculating a $90,000 startup cost and identifying a break-even point in Year 3. This experience allowed me to simulate a real-world consultancy role, where I didn't just study business theory but actually applied it to market research, operational logistics, and strategic financial modeling.

landing.title: Brayden Perry's Portfolio
landing.description: Showcasing strategic analysis, investment research, and professional insights through a variety of different projects and reports

about.intro:
Hello! Im Brayden Perry, a third-year Finance and Business Analytics student at Ohio University, where Im also pursuing a certificate in Banking and Financial Services.

On campus, Im actively involved in the Derivatives Management Group (DMG), where I conduct both fundamental research and technical analysis to evaluate securities such as stocks, bonds, and derivatives for weekly presentations. 

Im passionate about continuous learning and growth, and I pride myself on my adaptability and communication skills. Im always seeking new opportunities to expand my experience in finance and analytics, especially those that challenge me to think critically, solve complex problems, and make an impact in the financial industry.

jobs.title: Finance Intern
jobs.description: I worked on valuing municipal bonds and mortgage-backed securities using a Bloomberg Terminal to run breakeven assessments and help with portfolio recommendations. One of my main projects was building an automated Excel template for regulatory call reports, which saved a lot of time by cutting down on manual data entry and making the reporting process more accurate. I also helped out with quarter-end operations by validating data and making sure our documents were ready for audits

jobs.title: Head Analyst
jobs.description: As Head Analyst, I led a team of four to build investment pitches for U.S. Treasury futures and credit spreads. I spent a lot of time analyzing economic data like Core PCE and yield curve trends to figure out where interest rates were headed and how that would affect our positions. My goal was to take that complex financial data and turn it into clear, visual presentations that made our strategy easy for the group to understand.
